body:
Pretty sure I just failed my film history final, but on the upside, that means I’ve just got one easy final left, so now I can get back to writing! Problem is, I’m having trouble motivating myself to work on my ongoing Good Omens projects, so if anyone wants to send me short ficlet prompts, that’d be appreciated.

I’ll do ineffable husbands or gen stuff, and while I’d prefer SFW (just because most of my stuff has not been recently) I’m down for pretty much anything.

body: I think this is one of the more underrated moments in the book (and absolutely one of my favorites). I mean, yeah Aziraphale probably assumed Shadwell was looking for the shop next door but like…in a book full of extremely gay moments for Aziraphale, I think one of the gayest (other than his interactions with Crowley, of course), is how a man accuses him of seducing women and Aziraphale goes “I have never seduced a woman in my life.”

summary: aziraphale isn’t good with current trends, but he is good at dressing himself. likes luxurious fabrics, camelhair coats,...
body:
aziraphale isn’t good with current trends, but he is good at dressing himself. likes luxurious fabrics, camelhair coats, cashmere, etc etc. he’d be dressed remarkably well if it were decades earlier, would fit right in, only he’s ridiculously slow on the uptake. but there are those “born in the wrong era” folk who take a liking to him. ask where he purchased such and such coat. all for him to discuss, at length, some shop that used to sit nestled there on the corner …

and once, to his delight, a photographer for a “stylesofsoho” instagram page had taken his photo! crowley had been rather nonplussed to be shoved to the side, for once. finds himself exasperated by it in the years to come, if only because he’ll try to tell the angel that such and such trend went out of style ages ago. and aziraphale will only give this smug smile, “ah, yes, you’re right. i really should listen to you, crowley. especially since you were on the front page of The Instagram’s Fashion of Soho … oh, wait … that was me, wasn’t it, dear?” and crowley just grips the steering wheel because he’s realized it’s pointless to try and explain to the angel that instagram does not work like a newspaper, there is no front page.
